Austin_Animal_Center_Outcomes

I Visit the US government’s public data website and found a dataset I’m interested in which is named Austin Animal Center Outcomes, beacuse this dataset is about animal and I like animal very much, so I choose this dataset.

The dataset was metadata and was updated in March 8,2018, Animal Center Outcomes from Oct, 1st 2013 to present. Outcomes represent the status of animals as they leave the Animal Center. All animals receive a unique Animal ID during intake. Annually over 90% of animals entering the center, are adopted, transferred to rescue or returned to their owners. The Outcomes data set reflects that Austin, TX. is the largest “No Kill” city in the country.

The dataset has 79831 observation which is 79831 different animals, and 12 different variables, they are ‘Aninal.ID’,‘Name’,‘DateTime’,‘MonthYear’,‘Date.of.Birth’,‘Outcome.Type’,‘Outcome.Subtype’,‘Animal.type’,‘Sex.upon.Outcome’,‘Age.upon.outcome’,‘Breed’.

I plot the visualization about the Age for the animal and their type.
